Run nsdperf from M clients to/from N servers.
Requires pdsh to be installed, and passwordless ssh to/from all servers and clients.
--> Note: often times it is better to use the pdsh-rcmd-ssh instead of pdsh-rcmd-rsh package. If not, connection problems may result.

Usage:


RDMA:
./run-nsdperf.sh <serverList> <clientList> <rdmaDevice>

 - <serverlist> and <clientlist> are files that contain lists of server/client names, like an MPI hostfile
 - <rdmaDevice> is of the form hfi1_0:1, mlx5_0:1, etc

IPoIB/TCP:
./run-nsdperf-tcp.sh <serverList> <clientList>
 - <serverlist> and <clientlist> need to be the IP addresses or hostnames associated with the TCP network in test.
     For example, the IPoIB addresses for the hosts in test


Notes:
  - if nsdperf binary does not exist, it should compile automatically (see compile.sh)
  - you can edit run-nsdperf*sh files to define the message size and level of concurrency.
  - comment out "usecm on" if a proper ipoib network is not set up, or if you are using regular ethernet hostnames in the serverList and clientList
